   <body>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA"><a name="DUC8e07b5b82a5910058309dbeabd6a39d2"></a>Checking brake pad wear and replacing front brake pads
      </div>
      <div class="Attenzione"><img class="Attenzione" width="28" height="25" style="display: inline; float: none; left: 0.0; text-align: left; top: 0.0;" src="img/warning.jpg">Warning
      </div>
      <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2719"> </a>Clutch fluid is corrosive and will damage paint. Avoid contact with eyes and skin. In case of accidental contact, wash&nbsp;thoroughly
         with water.
      </div>
      <div class="Attenzione"><img class="Attenzione" width="28" height="25" style="display: inline; float: none; left: 0.0; text-align: left; top: 0.0;" src="img/important.jpg">Important
      </div>
      <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2722"> </a>On handing over the motorcycle after changing the brake pads, inform the customer that the front brake must be used gently
         for the first 100&nbsp;km to allow the pads to bed in completely.
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2725"> </a>Look through the slot in the calliper to make sure the groove in the brake pad friction material (1) is still visible.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="Attenzione"><img class="Attenzione" width="28" height="25" style="display: inline; float: none; left: 0.0; text-align: left; top: 0.0;" src="img/important.jpg">Important
      </div>
      <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2728"> </a>If either of the pads is worn, both pads must be renewed as a set.
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_4_012502844.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2733"> </a>Turn the pad retaining pins (1) clockwise.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_4_012602845.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2738"> </a>Remove the safety cotter pin (2).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_4_012702846.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2743"> </a>Withdraw the pad retaining pins (1) to the outside.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2745"> </a>Remove the clip (3) from between the two calliper halves.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_4_012802847.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2751"> </a>Force the calliper pistons back into their seats by forcing the old brake pads apart.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2753"> </a>Remove the worn pads (4).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_4_012902848.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="Attenzione"><img class="Attenzione" width="28" height="25" style="display: inline; float: none; left: 0.0; text-align: left; top: 0.0;" src="img/note.jpg">Note
      </div>
      <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2758"> </a>Change pads that have a shiny or “vitrified” appearance.
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2761"> </a>Fit the new pads and the clip (3), with the arrow pointing up.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_4_013002849.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2766"> </a>Fit the pads retaining pins (1) and fix them with safety cotter pins (2).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_4_013102850.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2771"> </a>Turn the pad retaining pins (1) counter clockwise.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_4_010302851.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2776"> </a>Operate the brake lever repeatedly so that the pads are firmly bedded in against the disc by the force of the brake fluid.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2778"> </a>Check that the level in the master cylinder tank is not below the MIN mark.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2780"> </a>If necessary, top up as follows.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2782"> </a>Turn the handlebar so that the reservoir is levelled.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2784"> </a>Remove the cover with membrane (5) of the front brake fluid reservoir (6) by unscrewing the screws (7).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2786"> </a>Top-up with specified fluid until reaching the Max. mark.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_4_013202852.jpg"></center>
      </div>
